The paper deals with algorithms for computing shortest paths in planar graphs, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper also introduces the concept of dense distance graphs, which has found numerous applications in planar graph algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also involves some theoretical analysis of the algorithms, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.LG (Learning) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
